## 🌐 Step 3: Frontend (HTML/CSS/JS on Vercel)

### Important JavaScript Parts

```javascript
const API = "https://machine-backend.vercel.app";

// LOAD ALL MACHINES — runs when page opens
async function loadMachines() {
    const response = await fetch(`${API}/machines`);
    const machines = await response.json();
    const tbody = document.getElementById("machineTable");
    tbody.innerHTML = "";

    machines.forEach(m => {
        tbody.innerHTML += `
            <tr>
                <td>${m.id}</td>
                <td>${m.machine_name}</td>
                <td>${m.status}</td>
                <td>
                    <button onclick="deleteMachine(${m.id})">Delete</button>
                </td>
            </tr>
        `;
    });
}

// ADD MACHINE — runs when form submitted
async function addMachine() {
    const data = {
        machine_name: document.getElementById("machine_name").value,
        machine_model: document.getElementById("machine_model").value,
        serial_number: document.getElementById("serial_number").value,
        location: document.getElementById("location").value,
        status: document.getElementById("status").value,
        ip_address: document.getElementById("ip_address").value
    };

    await fetch(`${API}/machines`, {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify(data)
    });

    loadMachines(); // Refresh table
}

// DELETE MACHINE — runs when delete button clicked
async function deleteMachine(id) {
    if (!confirm("Are you sure?")) return;
    await fetch(`${API}/machines/${id}`, { method: "DELETE" });
    loadMachines(); // Refresh table
}

// Load machines when page first opens
loadMachines();
```

#### Important Parts Explained

| Part                    | Meaning                                              |
|-------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| `const API`             | Backend URL — all requests go here                   |
| `async function`        | Function that waits for API response                 |
| `await fetch()`         | Call the API and wait for result                     |
| `response.json()`       | Convert API response to JavaScript object            |
| `tbody.innerHTML`       | Build HTML table rows from data                      |
| `machines.forEach()`    | Loop through each machine and create a table row     |
| `method: "POST"`        | Tell API we are sending new data                     |
| `method: "DELETE"`      | Tell API we want to delete data                      |
| `JSON.stringify(data)`  | Convert JS object to JSON string for sending         |
| `Content-Type: application/json` | Tell API we are sending JSON data         |
| `loadMachines()`        | Refresh the table after add/delete                   |
| `confirm()`             | Show popup asking user to confirm before delete      |

